FR940114-2-00108 FR940114-2-00065 Big Sandy Corridor Unit That Portion Lying Within Hardin and Tyler Counties Survey and Abstract No.: Mosley Baker; A&hyph;87. Portion: Part of A&hyph;87 within Hardin County described as follows: Beginning at the Northeast corner of said A&hyph;87; Thence, S. 02 ○45 ’ E., 800 feet, along the East line of A&hyph;87; Thence, N. 83 ○04 ’ W., 1400 feet; Thence, N. 03 ○00 ’ W., 1200 feet, along the West line of said A&hyph;87, to a point on the North line of Hardin County; Thence, East, 1000 feet along the North line of Hardin County; Thence, Southerly, approximately 800 feet along the westerly gradient boundary of Village Creek, to the Point of Beginning. Also, a part of A&hyph;87 within Tyler County, Beginning at the Northwest corner of said A&hyph;87; Thence, Easterly, approximately 1000 feet, along the southerly gradient boundary of Village Creek; Thence, West, 1000 feet, along the South line of Tyler County; Thence, N. 03 ○00 ’ W., 100 feet, along the West line of said A&hyph;87, to the Point of Beginning.
